### Architecture Review

#### Current State
```
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Overlapping Implementations (needs consolidation)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Multiple client files with similar functionality
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Duplicated configuration systems
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Scattered security implementations
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Good Separation (maintain)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Voice system (well-architected)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Tool abstractions (clean interface)
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ MCP integration (properly isolated)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Missing Components (needs addition)
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Proper state management
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Circuit breakers for resilience
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Caching layer for responses
```

#### Recommended Architecture
Based on our research, you should adopt:
```yaml
Core Layers:
  1. CLI Interface Layer (‚úÖ You have this)
  2. Agent Orchestrator (‚ö†Ô∏è Needs refinement)
  3. Router/Load Balancer (‚ùå Missing)
  4. Model Runtime Layer (‚ö†Ô∏è Only Ollama, needs LM Studio)
  5. Tool Execution Layer (‚úÖ Well implemented)
```

### Performance Analysis

#### Current Implementation
- Single-threaded execution model
- No response streaming optimization
- Missing context window management
- No token usage tracking

#### Recommended Optimizations
From our local model research:

```typescript
// Add streaming support
class OptimizedClient {
  async *streamGenerate(prompt: string) {
    const response = await fetch(`${this.endpoint}/api/generate`, {
      body: JSON.stringify({ 
        prompt, 
        stream: true,
        options: {
          num_gpu: -1,  // Use all GPU layers
          num_thread: 8,  // Parallel processing
        }
      })
    });
    
    for await (const chunk of response.body) {
      yield JSON.parse(chunk);
    }
  }
}

// Implement context window management
class ContextManager {
  private maxTokens = 4096;
  private contextWindow: Message[] = [];
  
  prune() {
    while (this.getTokenCount() > this.maxTokens * 0.8) {
      this.contextWindow.shift();
    }
  }
}
```

